<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>In a T-account, if reserves decrease by $1000, what else must change?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Deposits must decrease by $1000</option>
            <option letter="b">Loans must increase by $1000</option>
            <option letter="c">Nothing else needs to change</option>
            <option letter="d">Securities must increase by $1000</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>When reserves (an asset) decrease, there must be an equal decrease in deposits (a liability) to maintain the balance of the T-account.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What role did the IMF play in the Bretton Woods system?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It set exchange rates independently</option>
            <option letter="b">It provided loans to maintain fixed exchange rates</option>
            <option letter="c">It regulated gold prices</option>
            <option letter="d">It controlled world trade</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The IMF provided short-term loans to countries struggling to maintain their fixed exchange rates under the Bretton Woods system.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>What was a key argument of the Free Silver Movement?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Silver would cause deflation</option>
            <option letter="b">Silver would help creditors</option>
            <option letter="c">Silver would help debtors through inflation</option>
            <option letter="d">Silver would strengthen the dollar</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The Free Silver Movement argued that adding silver to the money supply would cause inflation, making it easier for debtors (especially farmers) to repay their loans.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>How does the Federal Reserve's discount window differ from open market operations?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">It involves direct lending to banks</option>
            <option letter="b">It only affects interest rates</option>
            <option letter="c">It requires congressional approval</option>
            <option letter="d">It only uses foreign currency</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The discount window involves the Fed directly lending to banks, while open market operations involve buying and selling securities in the open market.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>Under the gold standard, what was meant by "specie payments"?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Payment in paper money</option>
            <option letter="b">Payment in government bonds</option>
            <option letter="c">Payment in gold or silver coin</option>
            <option letter="d">Payment in foreign currency</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>Specie payments referred to the payment of obligations in physical gold or silver coin rather than in paper money or other substitutes.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
